**\[Experiment\] Suggest the Workspaces add-on to accounts that use multiple template types**  
**![:question:][image1]Why We Built It**  
We are exploring ways to recommend relevant features to customers based on their specific use cases. We know that the Workspaces add-on is used in various ways, with some customers leveraging it to organize work across multiple teams, departments, or even separate businesses. By this experiment we want to validate that customers who have templates from different use cases (Sales and HR) might benefit from using Workspaces add-on.  
![:bulb:][image2]**Hypothesis**  
If we target customers who have a single workspace but multiple template types (e.g., Sales invoices \+ HR contracts) and suggest the Workspaces add-on, then these customers are more likely to start a trial of add-on, find value in diversifying their work, and as a result will convert to a purchase.  
![:gear:][image3] **How It Works**

* Experiment relevant only to active and past due Business plan accounts who never started trial of Workspaces add-on before  
* Customers will see an inline suggestion that can be expanded into a hero card within the Document Lister, and they will have the option to dismiss it.  
* Main CTA will start the 7-day Workspaces add-on trial

![:bar\_chart:][image4] **Objective**

* Validating the hypothesis of targeted suggestion of certain add-ons  
* Increase number of customers trying Workspaces add-on  
* Add-on expansion MRR as a result of purchasing add-on after add-on trial

![:date:][image5] **Experiment details**

* Split name **exp\_growth\_experiment\_workspaces\_for\_different\_templates**  
* 17 November \- 100% rollout to Business accounts that fall into experiment logic  
* Live for 30 days, followed by data analysis afterwards

**\[Gradual Rollout\] Public Links Expiration Default — 2 Days**  
**![:information\_source:][image10] Why We Built It**  
**Currently, public document links expire after 60 days**, which poses a **security risk**. Some URL scanner services can index and store public links that remain active for months or even years. For example, [urlscan.io](http://urlscan.io/) once had 9K PandaDoc links accessible before we requested their removal. This means that anyone on the internet could access the link, creating potential data exposure and legal risk.  
To reduce this, we’re shortening the **default expiration period** for public links to **2 days**, following the recommendation from our Security team.  
![:gear:][image11] **How It Works**

* No action is required from users — new public links will **automatically expire after 2 days** by default.  
* When a recipient opens an expired link, they’ll see a [message](https://downloads.intercomcdn.com/i/o/xhbviy7k/1793687559/d584f86b4b992013af3150f81356/image.png?expires=1761976800&signature=f3a4c979b5a756ae9459b29722019ba93f1dd12a5571fb026f6c2a3c60fdbbba&req=dScuFc92moRaUPMW3nq%2Bge1YqKDVjeyR4%2Fmkqcs7d6kEryvTW0OjcKSaphda%0AKn%2BcYHq4xokP4kqjV9B8QUKmzk8%3D%0A): *“This link has expired”.* They can click **Get new link** to request a new access link (same behavior as today).  
* A new **[setting](https://downloads.intercomcdn.com/i/o/xhbviy7k/1791479587/6ab7d28286c576d3d098a3b2a632/image.png?expires=1761976800&signature=e6b68e0e8329795b852eb5e5f305b646c957dcf5cb8dea5dc50274030be179f1&req=dScuF815lIRXXvMW3nq%2BgVUCklp%2FyWwp20WyX%2BbEqTyAPHf7KXgMJ2S3UdjD%0AJeRTQhV6mpp%2Bk4QY1hiHf0%2BP3lY%3D%0A)** will be available to adjust the default expiration period to anywhere between **1–90 days**.

**⊞⊞⊞ \[QUOTE BUILDER\] Gradual Rollout: Enabled as Part of Business (10% Existing Users)**

***TL;DR***

We’re starting a **controlled rollout** that **unlocks sending with Quote Builder** for **10% of existing Business plan accounts**.

![:checkered\_flag:][image19] ***What’s changing?***

* **Existing Business:**  
  * Our Feature flag **enables “Send Doc” with Quote Builder** for a 10% treatment cohort.  
  * Pricing Table remains available; no forced migration.  
* **New Business:** 50% default to Quote Builder (PT also visible).  
* **Trials:** 100% enabled to send with Quote Builder (clear TRIAL in-app communication)  
* **Templates:** More templates will now include the Quote as a default instead of the Pricing Table.

Feature Flags: cpq\_advanced\_quotes\_trial , exp\_cpq\_advanced\_quote\_rollout  
![:flags:][image20] ***Why we’re doing this:***

* Reduce confusion from two quoting tools while **protecting Enterprise differentiation in the long-term**.  
* Validate **funnel health** and **Payments attach rate** with a statistically meaningful sample.  
* Build confidence for a broader transition away from the Pricing Table in 2026\.

![:traffic\_light:][image21] ***How we’re rolling out:***  
**Existing Business (non-CSM/AM):**

* 10% \-\> 20% \-\> 45% \-\> 100% (in the space of *8 Weeks*)

**New Business:**

* **Week 1:** 50% treatment → **Week 4:** 100%

**Trials:**

* **Week 1:** 100% treatment

(Flowchart attached in thread for a quick visual)

* **Adoption split:** % pricing docs using Quote Builder (goal ≥ 20% for new users by end of Q4)  
* **Funnel:** doc send & completion rates (QB vs PT)  
* **Revenue signals:** Payments attach, churn/downgrade/expansion checks

**\[FAKE DOOR EXPERIMENT:100% of all accounts\]**  
**![:dizzy:][image28]** '**Purchase' text copy instead of 'Send request to admin' for non-owners ![:dizzy:][image29]**  
**![:alphabet-white-question:][image30]Why we built it**

* Currently, only admin-owners can purchase plan upgrades or add-ons. Non-admin roles must send request to admins.  
* This setup assumes admins are the only stakeholders with budget authority, but in reality, many companies delegate budget decisions to other admins or managers.

Before investing in the full scope of changing permissions, we would like to run a fake door test where we test the intent of non-owners to click on the Purchase button  
**Our hypothesis is:** If non-admin roles are offered the option to purchase directly, we will see higher engagement and intent signals (measured by click-throughs), indicating latent demand. Removing admin-only restrictions could increase expansion revenue.  
![:gear:][image31] **How it works:**

* This is a fake door test: Non-owners WILL NOT be able to make any purchases  
* We have changed the text copy from 'Send request to admin' to 'Purchase' for all upsells for non-owners  
* By click on 'Purchase', the current 'send request to admin' flow will be triggered: admin-owner will receive the email with feature that needs to be unlocked

![:chart\_with\_upwards\_trend:][image32]  **Success Metrics**

* **Primary:** % of non-admins who click the “Purchase” button (purchase intent).  
* **Secondary:**  
  * % who drop off at the dialog  
  * A distribution of roles who clicked on ‘purchase’

The experiment will run 1 month, afterwards we will analyse it and make decision if we want to invest into granting purchasing permissions to other roles.

**\[EXPERIMENT:100% accounts\]**  
**![:sparkles:][image35] Smart recommendation section in Extensions store ![:sparkles:][image36]**  
Our hypothesis is: if we use pre-onboarding data and team characteristics to show more relevant features, then users will find valuable tools more easily, leading to higher upgrade intent and feature adoption.  
![:rocket:][image37] **Why we built it:**  
**We don't have personalisation in Extenstions store:** currently all integrations and add-ons are hardcoded in recommendation section. Our customers may feel that the recommendation is not tailored for their need and is not actually what they are using.  
![:gear:][image38] **How it works:**

* Personalised recommendation sections in Integration tab:  
  * We show tools that customer selected on pre-onboarding  
  * If customer selected Other/None or has no info from pre-onboarding \- we show our top integrations: Zapier, Stripe, Hubspot, SFDC  
* Personalised recommendation sections in Extensions tab:  
  * We show the list of add-ons depending on Sales, HR and Other solution from pre-onboarding  
  * Each subscription plan has it's own set of add-ons  
  * The mapping can be found [here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1yOozf4W2NAClh6l_hNnKrjsPFWbuNFkcEncd6sGUT-w/edit?gid=2016182384#gid=2016182384)

![:chart\_with\_upwards\_trend:][image39]  **Success Metrics**

* The % of users who open add-on cards from recommendations  
* Add-on Purchase Rate – % of add-on purchases initiated from the recommendation section)  
* Plan Upgrade Rate – % of plan upgrades initiated from recommendation section  
* Integration setup rate (from recommendation section)  \- % of accounts connecting integrations

The experiment will run 1 month, afterwards we will analyse it and adjust/iterate.

\[**Iteration 3: AB Test 'Pay as you go' in the Cancellation Flow**\]

**Signals from Iteration 2 (Final Report from Data team WIP):**

* **\>2.5x** the engagement against legacy coupon option  
* **\~3% pts.** higher save rate within the treatment group  
* Validated that the survey screen helps deflect **5-8%** of churn  
* No overage MRR yet from customers choosing PAYG i.e. churning customers choosing PAYG have \<5 doc need per month

**So what’s new?**

* Our latest initiative aims to further reduce in-product churn by introducing a **fake** "pure Pay as you go" plan in the cancellation flow.   
* The new offer is a **$0** upfront cost with **no** docs included but a pure usage-based charge of **$3** per document sent. 

**Why now?**

* This builds on our successful Phase 1 & 2 of PAYG.  
* The new offer is designed to align with customer needs and feedback on the Phase 1 & 2 PAYG:   
  * Churning users who didn't select PAYG noted that even a $15 subscription is an extra cost when the customer has no need to send docs and they'd rather reactivate when they actually need it.  
* With the new offer, we want to make it frictionless for a user to stay with PandaDoc and be the tool of choice should the churning user has a need to send a doc.

**Experiment Design**

* This is a fake door test; aka, such a plan doesn't exist yet.  
* 50% of churning customers will see the 'Launch' plan and 50% will see this new fake door offer.   
* Churning customers who select the new offer will be sent to our Free eSign plan which is more generous than what we advertise with this offer.

**Next Steps**

* If the test validates that such a plan further drives cancellation save rate, we will likely create such a plan and personalize the cancellation offers depending on the appropriate customer segments.
